headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 49 points, Khris Middleton had 26 points and 11 rebounds, and the Milwaukee Bucks edged Kevin Durant and the Brooklyn Nets 117-114 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo's 49 points pace Bucks past Nets

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum scored 10 of his 23 points in the fourth quarter and Portland held on for a 129-119 win over the Boston Celtics on Sunday night, extending the Trail Blazers' winning streak to four.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum powers Trail Blazers past Celtics 129-119

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo had 20 points and 10 rebounds, Jimmy Butler added 18 points, eight rebounds and eight assists, and the surging Miami Heat easily defeated the Charlotte Hornets 121-111 on Sunday night to move into sole possession of sixth place in the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat move into 6th place in East; beat Hornets 121-111

headlines.description: — Buddy Hield scored 27 points, Marvin Bagley III had 23 points and nine rebounds and Sacramento beat Dallas 111-99 on Sunday night, giving the also-ran Kings a season sweep of the playoff-contending Mavericks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Also-ran Kings beat contending Mavs 111-99 to finish sweep

events.name: New York Knicks at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 31 points in three quarters to lead the New York Knicks to a 122-97 victory over the Houston Rockets on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle scores 31 points as Knicks rout Rockets 122-97

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 32 points, and the Phoenix Suns held off the Oklahoma City Thunder 123-120 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 32 as Suns hold off Thunder 123-120

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 34 points and 12 rebounds, and the Philadelphia 76ers held on to beat the undermanned San Antonio Spurs 113-111 in overtime Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid, Sixers escape short-handed Spurs in OT, 113-111

events.name: Toronto Raptors at Los Angeles Lakers
